														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4865854">
									

<p>I feel like you've definitely got a fun setting for a story here; but I don't really have a strong feeling for what you're actually like, doing here? Specifically: it seems like you're spending a lot of time interviewing the SCP and like showing off how amusing they are but my concern is that this doesn't really like&#8230; go anywhere? There's no big emotional or narrative arc within these interviews and so you're left kinda relying on them being interesting enough alone to carry this and&#8230;I'm not sure they will be?</p>
<p>There's definitely elements I like e.g. the exploration of the like, kinda paranoia you get working at the Foundation if they're willing to kill you for breaking a rule; and the whole angle of the demon being so annoying hell is glad they're gone; and I just&#8230;kinda want to see you tell more of a complete story around these and really use these elements to&#8230;do something?</p>

							</div>

								
					
